1
00:00:19,666 --> 00:00:21,666
[projector whirring]

2
00:00:35,583 --> 00:00:37,883
["Where Do You Go"
by Claire George playing]

3
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:58,170
<i>♪ Time breathed slower ♪</i>

4
00:00:58,250 --> 00:01:00,750
<i>♪ When we were younger ♪</i>

5
00:01:03,708 --> 00:01:07,918
<i>♪ And now it's racing so fast... ♪</i>

6
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:13,003
[music continues playing
through headphones]

7
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,540
[distant horn honking]

8
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,460
[water flowing]

9
00:01:50,375 --> 00:01:51,785
-What are you doing?
-[gasps]

10
00:01:51,875 --> 00:01:53,325
[breathing heavily]

11
00:01:58,750 --> 00:01:59,830
Violet Markey?

12
00:02:02,375 --> 00:02:03,455
Oh, my God.

13
00:02:10,583 --> 00:02:11,583
Please go.

14
00:02:13,083 --> 00:02:15,253
-Well, I don't think that's very--
-Just go!

15
00:02:31,291 --> 00:02:32,631
[Violet] What are you doing?

16
00:02:33,041 --> 00:02:34,171
I asked you first.

17
00:02:36,291 --> 00:02:37,791
[chuckling]

18
00:02:38,125 --> 00:02:39,665
This is higher than I thought.

19
00:02:44,666 --> 00:02:45,496
Hey.

20
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:47,708
Hey, look.

21
00:02:48,625 --> 00:02:49,785
Look what I can do.

22
00:02:51,791 --> 00:02:53,541
Stop. Stop!

23
00:03:05,166 --> 00:03:06,166
Hey, Violet.

24
00:03:20,958 --> 00:03:22,248
[breathing shakily]

25
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,080
["The Mountaintop"
by PaintSmooke playing]

26
00:03:56,958 --> 00:03:58,958
[indistinct chattering]

27
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:07,880
Hey. Do you have plans this weekend?
My parents are gonna be out of town.

28
00:04:07,958 --> 00:04:10,378
I was thinking about having a party
or something.

29
00:04:16,541 --> 00:04:17,421
Violet?

30
00:04:18,791 --> 00:04:19,631
You OK?

31
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:25,253
[man] How's everything going?

32
00:04:26,208 --> 00:04:27,918
"Everything" is a really big word.

33
00:04:28,916 --> 00:04:31,376
-Let's start with--
-[boy] Do you mean physically?

34
00:04:31,458 --> 00:04:34,168
Emotionally?
Those both could encompass "everything."

35
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:36,080
Or is "everything" encompassed
by both things?

36
00:04:36,166 --> 00:04:37,916
Are you feeling overwhelmed by anything?

37
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,750
If "everything" is encompassed
by both things,

38
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:42,133
are they a part of our reality,
or are they somewhere else?

39
00:04:42,208 --> 00:04:43,668
This isn't funny, Theodore.

40
00:04:45,416 --> 00:04:46,246
Finch.

41
00:04:47,625 --> 00:04:49,785
I need you
to take these meetings seriously.

42
00:04:49,875 --> 00:04:50,875
I get it.

43
00:04:51,583 --> 00:04:53,753
OK, do you "get"
that you're on probation,

44
00:04:54,791 --> 00:04:56,541
and in danger of not graduating?

45
00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:01,330
You've already missed
two weeks of school this year.

46
00:05:01,958 --> 00:05:02,998
Yeah, um...

47
00:05:04,416 --> 00:05:06,126
-my grandma--
-Stop one second.

48
00:05:06,208 --> 00:05:07,918
I just wanna clarify real quickly.

49
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:11,130
Is this the grandma who's died four times
over the past three years?

50
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,330
Five times, actually.

51
00:05:14,083 --> 00:05:15,173
This is the fifth.

52
00:05:18,625 --> 00:05:19,875
She's our miracle.

53
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:25,000
I really wanna help you,
but you've gotta take this seriously.

54
00:05:26,291 --> 00:05:30,541
I mean, you agreed to these terms,
these weekly counseling sessions,

55
00:05:30,625 --> 00:05:33,375
maintaining a B-average,
extracurricular participation.

56
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:35,498
And I am loving pottery.

57
00:05:36,125 --> 00:05:37,125
Come on, man.

58
00:05:37,583 --> 00:05:38,713
Look, I get it.

59
00:05:38,791 --> 00:05:40,921
If I screw anything up, I'm out.

60
00:05:41,666 --> 00:05:43,536
We're not askin' a lot of you, Finch.

61
00:05:45,083 --> 00:05:46,383
You just need to show up.

62
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,460
[girl] My parents are pissed
because I missed early admissions,

63
00:05:50,541 --> 00:05:52,131
but it's not like that matters, anyway.

64
00:05:52,208 --> 00:05:54,128
I mean, I know I'm gonna get in.

65
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:57,923
Did you apply anywhere yet?

66
00:05:59,208 --> 00:06:01,078
-Hey.
-Hi.

67
00:06:01,625 --> 00:06:03,875
So, you going to Amanda's party?

68
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:06,383
[boy] It'll be fun.

69
00:06:07,125 --> 00:06:08,205
So I've heard.

70
00:06:08,625 --> 00:06:10,625
It couldn't hurt
to have a little fun, right?

71
00:06:11,208 --> 00:06:15,128
Yo, do you think it'd be weird
if I named my kid after a famous person?

72
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:18,668
Like, if I named him Danny DeVito Donahue,

73
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:21,420
do you...
do you think he'd be mad about it?

74
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:23,875
Is "DeVito" the middle name?

75
00:06:24,458 --> 00:06:25,328
Yeah.

76
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:27,875
Follow-up question:
how high are you right now?

77
00:06:27,958 --> 00:06:28,958
[giggling]

78
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:33,250
On the scale,
I'd probably say very... this way.

79
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:35,213
-[Finch] On the scale...
-[boy] Yeah?

80
00:06:37,083 --> 00:06:38,463
What are you looking at?

81
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:42,250
Just admiring the social norms
of teenage angst.

82
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:45,043
-Are you looking at Violet Markey?
-Yep.

83
00:06:46,250 --> 00:06:47,080
Her, um...

84
00:06:48,250 --> 00:06:49,460
her sister died, right?

85
00:06:50,458 --> 00:06:51,328
Yeah, dude.

86
00:06:51,416 --> 00:06:52,286
Hm.

87
00:06:53,083 --> 00:06:54,633
Why ask about her all of a sudden?

88
00:06:54,708 --> 00:06:56,208
I'm intrigued.
A guy can't be intrigued?

89
00:06:56,291 --> 00:06:59,541
Well, a guy can be intrigued.
You being intrigued is weird.

90
00:07:00,125 --> 00:07:03,075
-[boy] Definitely weird.
-No, I don't think it's weird.

91
00:07:03,166 --> 00:07:04,326
I wouldn't say "weird."

92
00:07:04,416 --> 00:07:06,496
Wait, if you don't think you're weird,
well...

93
00:07:07,875 --> 00:07:10,325
-Yeah, that's true. Very true.
-[boy] She has a point.

94
00:07:12,541 --> 00:07:13,711
[tires screech]

95
00:07:19,583 --> 00:07:22,463
-[woman] Your guidance counselor called.
-Embryo?

96
00:07:22,541 --> 00:07:23,421
[woman] What?

97
00:07:24,375 --> 00:07:25,455
[Finch chuckles]

98
00:07:25,541 --> 00:07:29,461
His name's Embry. I call him Embryo.
It's the little things, Kate.

99
00:07:29,541 --> 00:07:31,631
Did you do something
I should be worried about?

100
00:07:31,708 --> 00:07:34,378
I'm genuinely offended
by that supposition.

101
00:07:34,916 --> 00:07:36,246
-Finch.
-No.

102
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,500
It's fine. I'll deal with it.

103
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:40,753
-[Kate] I hate when you say that.
-Why?

104
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:44,083
Because what you really mean is
that I'm gonna have to deal with it.

105
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:47,710
Did you cut class again?

106
00:07:47,791 --> 00:07:49,381
No! For fuck's sake,

107
00:07:49,458 --> 00:07:52,208
just go hang out with Tina
or whatever it is you do.

108
00:07:52,291 --> 00:07:53,171
I'm fine.

109
00:07:54,083 --> 00:07:57,333
OK. I'm gonna be home late.
There's food in the fridge.

110
00:07:57,416 --> 00:07:59,126
-Mm-hmm.
-Real food, Finch.

111
00:07:59,833 --> 00:08:00,713
Where's Mom?

112
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:03,041
She had to go to Chicago for business.
Remember?

113
00:08:03,125 --> 00:08:05,285
-Oh, yeah, right. Cool.
-Love you.

114
00:08:05,583 --> 00:08:06,503
[Finch] Hey.

115
00:08:10,583 --> 00:08:11,833
-Love you.
-Love you.

116
00:08:13,541 --> 00:08:15,381
[Kate] No more cheese, Finch!

117
00:08:28,208 --> 00:08:29,668
I'm gonna get the dessert.

118
00:08:35,625 --> 00:08:38,785
[Dad] Your mother and I know
that today couldn't have been easy.

119
00:08:39,708 --> 00:08:41,828
And it wasn't easy for us either.

120
00:08:46,541 --> 00:08:48,961
-If you need to talk about it--
-[door opens]

121
00:08:49,458 --> 00:08:50,958
[footsteps approaching]

122
00:08:51,625 --> 00:08:53,415
[Mom] I thought this would be nice.

123
00:09:05,875 --> 00:09:07,625
I've been making it for 19 years.

124
00:09:18,666 --> 00:09:21,666
["Mo' Better Blues"
by Branford Marsalis Quartet playing]

125
00:09:33,958 --> 00:09:35,498
[scribbling]

126
00:10:05,666 --> 00:10:07,376
[keyboard keys clattering]

127
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:38,083
["Tank Town" by Many Voices Speak plays
through headphones]

128
00:11:04,791 --> 00:11:06,791
[chalk scratching on chalkboard]

129
00:11:11,958 --> 00:11:13,668
[teacher] As some of you
will be graduating

130
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:15,420
and leaving us at the end of the year,

131
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:19,210
I feel an obligation to make sure
you see the wondrous sights of Indiana

132
00:11:19,291 --> 00:11:20,381
while you can.

133
00:11:20,458 --> 00:11:23,458
To wander them, if you will.

134
00:11:24,458 --> 00:11:28,788
For your class project, you must report
on two or more wonders of Indiana.

135
00:11:28,875 --> 00:11:30,495
You will write about them,

136
00:11:30,583 --> 00:11:33,753
explain their significance
to you and to Indiana,

137
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:35,463
and why you chose to visit them.

138
00:11:36,125 --> 00:11:38,245
I want you to take time
on this assignment.

139
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:39,503
Be thoughtful.

140
00:11:39,583 --> 00:11:41,043
[students laughing]

141
00:11:42,458 --> 00:11:43,288
[teacher] OK.

142
00:11:44,958 --> 00:11:45,958
What just happened?

143
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:47,960
That was so weird.

144
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:49,501
-What?
-[teacher] All right, settle.

145
00:11:49,583 --> 00:11:50,633
Violet, are you OK?

146
00:11:51,708 --> 00:11:54,538
All right, let's take our seats.
Let's focus up.

147
00:11:55,166 --> 00:11:56,916
If you're done, Mr. Finch?

148
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:01,040
Yes, I am done, and can I just say you
are doing a fine job teaching this class.

149
00:12:01,125 --> 00:12:03,125
My young brain is plump with knowledge.

150
00:12:03,916 --> 00:12:06,206
-[teacher] Thank you, Mr. Finch.
-You're welcome.

151
00:12:06,708 --> 00:12:08,168
[teacher] As I was saying,

152
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:11,960
you'll be taking photos,
doing some drawings, capturing detail.

153
00:12:12,041 --> 00:12:14,751
You will be doing this in teams of two.

154
00:12:16,041 --> 00:12:17,461
Can we choose our partners?

155
00:12:17,875 --> 00:12:18,995
Yes, Mr. Finch.

156
00:12:21,958 --> 00:12:22,788
Hey.

157
00:12:25,916 --> 00:12:26,916
So, um...

158
00:12:27,958 --> 00:12:31,498
do you think that there's such a thing
as a perfect day?

159
00:12:32,791 --> 00:12:34,881
I'm the last person you should be asking.

160
00:12:42,666 --> 00:12:43,706
[microwave pings]

161
00:12:59,708 --> 00:13:01,378
[Violet]<i> For my geography class,</i>

162
00:13:01,458 --> 00:13:05,128
this teacher wants us to do this project
with a partner,

163
00:13:05,208 --> 00:13:07,288
and I just don't wanna do it.

164
00:13:07,708 --> 00:13:10,128
Well, did you ask
for an alternate project?

165
00:13:10,875 --> 00:13:12,745
Yeah, he just... he wouldn't listen.

166
00:13:13,583 --> 00:13:15,253
Well, maybe it's time
to get back out there.

167
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:17,330
That's the same thing he said.

168
00:13:19,958 --> 00:13:21,168
I know it's hard.

169
00:13:22,666 --> 00:13:25,326
-But you just don't go out anymore.
-That's not true.

170
00:13:25,416 --> 00:13:27,786
When's the last time you hung out
with your friends?

171
00:13:29,250 --> 00:13:32,580
I think it would be really good
if you'd spend some time with them.

172
00:13:34,166 --> 00:13:37,626
So, if I hung out with my friends,
you'd get me outta this assignment?

173
00:13:37,958 --> 00:13:38,958
[chuckles]

174
00:13:39,583 --> 00:13:41,253
["Parade" by Sylvan Esso playing]

175
00:13:41,333 --> 00:13:44,423
<i>♪ Speedy, speedy, slow down time</i>
<i>Gas station is running dry ♪</i>

176
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:47,170
<i>♪ Mm-hmm, eh eh, mm-hmm ♪</i>

177
00:13:48,458 --> 00:13:52,378
<i>♪ Sweaty, sweaty, wonder why</i>
<i>Now it's always summer time ♪</i>

178
00:13:52,458 --> 00:13:53,378
Violet!

179
00:13:55,791 --> 00:13:58,081
-[Amanda] You came.
-[Violet] I did.

180
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:00,003
-[girl] Hey.
-Hi.

181
00:14:00,416 --> 00:14:03,166
-I'm gonna get a drink. Do you want one?
-I'm good.

182
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:04,630
Come on, babe.

183
00:14:05,166 --> 00:14:06,126
OK.

184
00:14:23,791 --> 00:14:25,041
[gasping]

185
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:36,501
[groaning, laughter]

186
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:43,333
[sighs]

187
00:14:47,041 --> 00:14:47,881
Yeah...

188
00:14:47,958 --> 00:14:49,958
["Yeah Right" by Joji playing]

189
00:14:53,208 --> 00:14:54,708
[water pouring out]

190
00:14:54,791 --> 00:14:55,831
[faucet running]

191
00:14:58,416 --> 00:14:59,496
Hey.

192
00:15:01,125 --> 00:15:02,455
That's a heavy pour.

193
00:15:03,083 --> 00:15:04,713
You know me. I love to rage.

194
00:15:04,791 --> 00:15:07,881
[chuckles] So, you wanna go out back?
Talk a little?

195
00:15:10,291 --> 00:15:12,711
I think I'm gonna leave pretty soon,
actually.

196
00:15:13,375 --> 00:15:16,125
Really? But... I mean, I just got here.

197
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,498
It's just all a little much, you know?

198
00:15:21,208 --> 00:15:23,458
How much longer
are you gonna act like this?

199
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:27,625
It's been months.
When are you gonna just...

200
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:33,670
Nice.

201
00:15:35,666 --> 00:15:38,416
Violet, you know
I didn't mean it like that. Just...

202
00:15:39,583 --> 00:15:41,543
[dog barking in distance]

203
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:47,245
[cell phone vibrating]

204
00:15:57,708 --> 00:16:01,418
[Finch] <i>Violet Markey,</i>
<i>if you're seeing this, you're still alive.</i>

205
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:02,710
<i>Please call to confirm.</i>

206
00:16:03,166 --> 00:16:05,786
<i>765-276-8504.</i>

207
00:16:06,666 --> 00:16:10,956
[singing]
<i>♪ I met you standin' on a ledge ♪</i>

208
00:16:11,041 --> 00:16:14,331
<i>♪ What's going on</i>
<i>Inside that pretty head?</i> ♪

209
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:18,831
<i>♪ I met you standing on a ledge ♪</i>

210
00:16:18,916 --> 00:16:23,536
<i>♪ Why don't you come talk to me instead? ♪</i>

211
00:16:24,291 --> 00:16:25,791
[cell phone vibrating]

212
00:16:31,708 --> 00:16:32,828
Theodore Finch speaking.

213
00:16:32,916 --> 00:16:34,166
Take it down now.

214
00:16:36,708 --> 00:16:40,998
The video will self-destruct
in three, two...

215
00:16:42,291 --> 00:16:43,291
<i>...please refresh.</i>

216
00:16:46,541 --> 00:16:47,711
Why would you do that?

217
00:16:48,125 --> 00:16:49,745
I wanna talk about the bridge.

218
00:16:53,291 --> 00:16:57,211
[Finch] <i>"I feel we can't go through</i>
<i>another of those terrible times."</i>

219
00:17:00,416 --> 00:17:03,166
One morning barely qualifies
as a terrible time.

220
00:17:03,541 --> 00:17:04,831
It's a quote.

221
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:06,830
Virginia Woolf.

222
00:17:08,791 --> 00:17:09,671
OK.

223
00:17:11,208 --> 00:17:12,208
Can I come over?

224
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:14,253
[Violet]<i> Now?</i>

225
00:17:15,291 --> 00:17:16,381
Yeah.

226
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:28,380
So...

227
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:31,003
I Googled you.

228
00:17:33,958 --> 00:17:35,328
You <i>Googled </i>me?

229
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:39,630
Yeah, what's with that...

230
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:43,130
the website that you have
with your sister?

231
00:17:44,958 --> 00:17:45,878
Had.

232
00:17:50,458 --> 00:17:52,538
I read some of your stuff.
It's really good.

233
00:17:53,875 --> 00:17:55,125
I don't write anymore.

234
00:17:58,583 --> 00:18:01,793
So, you moved here from California.

235
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:05,333
How was that?

236
00:18:06,666 --> 00:18:08,166
California to Indiana?

237
00:18:09,125 --> 00:18:10,415
Must've been different.

238
00:18:12,125 --> 00:18:12,955
Yeah.

239
00:18:23,375 --> 00:18:25,125
I didn't know that it happened there.

240
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:27,750
At the bridge.

241
00:18:31,083 --> 00:18:32,713
I'm not, you know...

242
00:18:35,583 --> 00:18:36,923
Suicidal?

243
00:18:37,791 --> 00:18:38,791
You can say it.

244
00:18:39,500 --> 00:18:40,500
Well, I'm not.

245
00:18:42,458 --> 00:18:45,208
Whatever you are, I saved your life.

246
00:18:48,083 --> 00:18:49,253
No, you didn't.

247
00:18:50,666 --> 00:18:52,826
You're making a big deal out of nothing.

248
00:18:53,416 --> 00:18:55,626
Mm... kinda looked like somethin'.

249
00:18:58,250 --> 00:18:59,710
What do you want from me?

250
00:19:00,875 --> 00:19:03,875
I was just thinkin' that
we should be partners.

251
00:19:04,583 --> 00:19:06,043
For the wandering project.

252
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:09,080
I think it would be good for you
to get out.

253
00:19:10,125 --> 00:19:11,535
Maybe I don't wanna get out.

254
00:19:12,625 --> 00:19:14,125
