01:03:54,208 --> 01:03:55,828
[Violet pants]

766
01:04:02,000 --> 01:04:04,130
Tell me something real about you.

767
01:04:06,208 --> 01:04:07,328
Or I'm leaving.

768
01:04:07,916 --> 01:04:09,036
OK.

769
01:04:10,500 --> 01:04:14,000
Sometimes I have to go to places
that make me feel like myself.

770
01:04:14,083 --> 01:04:18,543
I need to do things that remind me
that I'm in control.

771
01:04:26,875 --> 01:04:28,125
My dad used to...

772
01:04:29,708 --> 01:04:31,208
get in these dark moods.

773
01:04:37,875 --> 01:04:39,205
Did he do that to you?

774
01:04:43,958 --> 01:04:45,668
I used to be a lot smaller.

775
01:04:50,458 --> 01:04:52,788
I used to not know
how to get out of the way.

776
01:04:59,750 --> 01:05:01,540
People don't like messy, right?

777
01:05:02,666 --> 01:05:04,666
[gentle instrumental music playing]

778
01:05:21,250 --> 01:05:22,710
[rain pattering]

779
01:05:31,333 --> 01:05:32,463
[Violet giggles]

780
01:05:48,583 --> 01:05:50,003
[both laughing]

781
01:05:50,125 --> 01:05:51,705
-[Violet] Uh...
-[Finch] Yeah.

782
01:05:51,791 --> 01:05:54,211
-Oh, wait. Yeah, you got it.
-I know, I had it!

783
01:05:54,291 --> 01:05:58,961
[both singing]
<i>♪ I met you standin' on a ledge ♪</i>

784
01:05:59,250 --> 01:06:03,790
<i>♪ What's going on</i>
<i>Inside that pretty head? ♪</i>

785
01:06:03,875 --> 01:06:08,535
<i>♪ I met you standin' on a ledge ♪</i>

786
01:06:08,875 --> 01:06:14,955
<i>♪ Why don't you come talk to me instead? ♪</i>

787
01:06:15,041 --> 01:06:17,881
-[Violet giggles] And then it goes--
-There's the bridge.

788
01:06:19,833 --> 01:06:20,793
[Finch] <i>♪ I... ♪</i>

789
01:06:20,875 --> 01:06:22,205
-Yeah. No, you got it.
-OK.

790
01:06:22,291 --> 01:06:26,631
[both singing]<i> ♪ I met you ♪</i>

791
01:06:27,208 --> 01:06:30,668
<i>♪ I met you</i> ♪

792
01:06:31,416 --> 01:06:37,576
<i>♪ I met you standin' on a ledge ♪</i>

793
01:06:39,333 --> 01:06:41,383
-[thunder rumbling]
-[Finch chuckles]

794
01:06:42,875 --> 01:06:44,875
[gentle instrumental music playing]

795
01:08:04,333 --> 01:08:05,633
[gasps] Finch.

796
01:08:06,041 --> 01:08:07,961
Finch, wake up. We gotta go.

797
01:08:08,791 --> 01:08:09,791
[Finch] Oh, shit!

798
01:08:13,791 --> 01:08:16,211
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. My phone died.

799
01:08:16,291 --> 01:08:17,501
Violet, inside.

800
01:08:17,583 --> 01:08:19,963
-Finch, just... you should go home.
-[Finch] Don't blame her.

801
01:08:20,041 --> 01:08:22,211
-If I could explain. Please--
-It's not his fault!

802
01:08:22,291 --> 01:08:23,171
Just get in the house.

803
01:08:23,250 --> 01:08:25,170
-We'll talk about it later.
-I lost track of time.

804
01:08:25,250 --> 01:08:26,330
-Finch!
-If I could--

805
01:08:27,875 --> 01:08:29,915
I'm so... I'm so sorry.

806
01:08:30,833 --> 01:08:32,923
It was my fault. I fucked up.

807
01:08:33,000 --> 01:08:36,710
Please, just don't blame her. Please.
I'm sorry.

808
01:08:36,791 --> 01:08:38,921
Just... go home.

809
01:08:53,750 --> 01:08:54,880
[message alert pings]

810
01:09:01,166 --> 01:09:02,326
[message alert pings]

811
01:09:02,708 --> 01:09:03,788
[Finch sighs]

812
01:09:36,333 --> 01:09:38,633
[breathing heavily]

813
01:09:43,083 --> 01:09:44,463
[Mom] Do you have any clue

814
01:09:45,583 --> 01:09:48,923
what horrible situations we had you in,
in our heads?

815
01:09:50,666 --> 01:09:53,576
You have to understand how that felt,

816
01:09:54,375 --> 01:09:56,785
your dad and I not knowing where you were.

817
01:09:58,750 --> 01:10:00,170
I said I was sorry.

818
01:10:00,958 --> 01:10:02,878
But you didn't have to treat Finch
like that.

819
01:10:02,958 --> 01:10:05,828
Well, he's the boy
that kept our daughter out all night.

820
01:10:07,041 --> 01:10:09,131
I kept him out all night, too, Mom.

821
01:10:17,916 --> 01:10:19,916
["November" by Babeheaven playing]

822
01:10:48,375 --> 01:10:49,995
[music continues]

823
01:11:42,041 --> 01:11:42,881
Hey.

824
01:11:43,250 --> 01:11:45,500
Hey, V. Hey, what's up?

825
01:11:46,250 --> 01:11:47,170
How are you?

826
01:11:48,000 --> 01:11:49,960
-Fine.
-It's been a minute. What's been going on?

827
01:11:50,041 --> 01:11:51,501
I can't deal with you right now.

828
01:11:52,833 --> 01:11:54,133
Is everything OK?

829
01:11:54,916 --> 01:11:56,666
Honestly, I don't know.

830
01:11:58,708 --> 01:12:00,038
I'm not tryin' to be an asshole,

831
01:12:00,125 --> 01:12:01,875
but you should know
what you're getting into.

832
01:12:03,333 --> 01:12:05,383
-I do.
-No, you don't.

833
01:12:05,458 --> 01:12:06,458
-He--
-Let's go.

834
01:12:07,000 --> 01:12:09,330
-Where've you been?
-You know why she's hangin' out with you?

835
01:12:09,416 --> 01:12:10,496
She's tryin' to fix you.

836
01:12:10,583 --> 01:12:12,923
Shut up, Roamer! Just...

837
01:12:13,083 --> 01:12:16,333
[Roamer] You have no idea
who he really is, do you? He's a freak!

838
01:12:17,583 --> 01:12:19,963
-Call me a freak one more time.
-You're a fuckin' freak.

839
01:12:20,041 --> 01:12:22,041
[students gasping, exclaiming]

840
01:12:23,041 --> 01:12:23,961
[Violet] Finch!

841
01:12:24,291 --> 01:12:25,131
Finch!

842
01:12:25,208 --> 01:12:26,208
[Violet] Stop!

843
01:12:27,041 --> 01:12:28,001
Finch!

844
01:12:30,125 --> 01:12:32,245
Finch! Yo, let him go, man. Get off him.

845
01:12:33,791 --> 01:12:35,921
Finch, stop! Stop!

846
01:12:38,750 --> 01:12:40,540
[Roamer gasping for breath]

847
01:12:40,833 --> 01:12:42,003
[girl 1] Oh, my God!

848
01:12:42,083 --> 01:12:44,293
[girl 2] What the hell?
He almost killed him.

849
01:12:44,375 --> 01:12:46,245
[students muttering]

850
01:12:56,583 --> 01:12:57,753
[boy] He's crazy.

851
01:13:16,875 --> 01:13:17,705
Fuck!

852
01:13:18,875 --> 01:13:20,625
Fuck! Fuck! Fuck!

853
01:13:37,083 --> 01:13:37,963
Anything?

854
01:13:42,541 --> 01:13:43,921
Guess he's gone again.

855
01:13:47,916 --> 01:13:50,076
I've been friends with the guy
since minute one,

856
01:13:51,250 --> 01:13:53,330
and I haven't waited
for his call in years.

857
01:13:54,000 --> 01:13:54,960
He just...

858
01:13:56,541 --> 01:13:58,461
gets in this mood sometimes, and...

859
01:13:59,583 --> 01:14:01,753
it's hard, you know?

860
01:14:03,750 --> 01:14:04,830
He's not easy,

861
01:14:06,166 --> 01:14:08,876
and everybody who gets close to him
gets burned out.

862
01:14:12,750 --> 01:14:14,290
So, why do you stick around?

863
01:14:16,041 --> 01:14:17,041
[he sighs]

864
01:14:19,666 --> 01:14:20,746
Because...

865
01:14:23,916 --> 01:14:24,916
'cause I love him.

866
01:14:26,875 --> 01:14:30,035
He thinks everybody leaves him
and I won't do that.

867
01:14:32,208 --> 01:14:33,628
This is what we do.

868
01:14:34,333 --> 01:14:37,883
I'm gonna get mad,
he's gonna come back and apologize,

869
01:14:37,958 --> 01:14:40,038
and it'll be like it never even happened.

870
01:14:51,958 --> 01:14:52,958
Hey.

871
01:14:54,083 --> 01:14:55,963
Is... is Finch here?

872
01:14:56,958 --> 01:14:58,248
Did something happen?

873
01:15:00,958 --> 01:15:02,168
[Kate] Yeah, come on in.

874
01:15:06,250 --> 01:15:07,380
[girl] I'm Lindsay.

875
01:15:07,458 --> 01:15:11,828
Um... I'm OCD and just got diagnosed
with a social anxiety disorder,

876
01:15:11,916 --> 01:15:14,666
so being here with everyone
is not intimidating at all.

877
01:15:14,750 --> 01:15:15,960
[scattered chuckling]

878
01:15:17,208 --> 01:15:19,458
Last year, I started cutting myself.

879
01:15:20,625 --> 01:15:23,995
I still deal with it, but I'm here.

880
01:15:25,250 --> 01:15:26,750
I'm so sorry.

881
01:15:26,833 --> 01:15:28,133
No worries. Have a seat.

882
01:15:32,666 --> 01:15:34,286
[boy] Hi, I'm Bradley.

883
01:15:34,375 --> 01:15:40,995
Um... I am ADHD, OCD,
BPD, DID, and bipolar.

884
01:15:41,541 --> 01:15:42,501
Yeah. [chuckles]

885
01:15:42,833 --> 01:15:46,463
Um... you'd think some of those
would cancel the others out, but...

886
01:15:47,041 --> 01:15:48,671
Yeah, my week's been OK.

887
01:15:48,750 --> 01:15:50,920
I've been watching
a lot of basketball lately,

888
01:15:51,000 --> 01:15:53,290
and that's been helping a lot, so...

889
01:15:54,000 --> 01:15:54,830
Good.

890
01:15:56,458 --> 01:15:57,918
Hi. Welcome.

891
01:16:01,875 --> 01:16:02,875
Um...

892
01:16:05,041 --> 01:16:07,671
I'm, uh... Theodore Finch.

893
01:16:09,791 --> 01:16:10,831
No labels.

894
01:16:12,583 --> 01:16:16,133
Not really sure why I'm here.
[chuckles lightly]

895
01:16:17,166 --> 01:16:18,126
Uh...

896
01:16:20,291 --> 01:16:25,041
I guess it's 'cause I...
I got in this fight at school and,

897
01:16:26,500 --> 01:16:27,540
like,

898
01:16:28,875 --> 01:16:31,535
I was there, but I wasn't there.

899
01:16:31,625 --> 01:16:33,625
I was watchin' myself, and...

900
01:16:37,875 --> 01:16:38,825
uh...

901
01:16:39,458 --> 01:16:41,828
I-I-I just get a little lost sometimes.

902
01:16:45,000 --> 01:16:47,330
I run... a lot.

903
01:16:48,041 --> 01:16:49,461
Sometimes that helps.

904
01:16:51,000 --> 01:16:52,000
Kind of.

905
01:16:56,250 --> 01:16:57,710
I don't know. Is that enough?

906
01:16:58,666 --> 01:16:59,536
Sure.

907
01:17:00,125 --> 01:17:01,745
Thanks. Glad you're here.

908
01:17:05,458 --> 01:17:07,828
Amanda, why don't you go ahead?

909
01:17:10,166 --> 01:17:11,246
I'm Amanda.

910
01:17:13,750 --> 01:17:14,790
I'm bulimic.

911
01:17:16,291 --> 01:17:18,131
I've tried to kill myself twice.

912
01:17:21,375 --> 01:17:23,285
I think about it almost every day.

913
01:17:37,166 --> 01:17:38,876
[footsteps approaching]

914
01:17:39,416 --> 01:17:41,416
[Kate] Hey, have you heard anything yet?

915
01:17:42,125 --> 01:17:44,325
-No.
-[Kate sighs] OK.

916
01:17:45,458 --> 01:17:48,418
I gotta go to work. I'm gonna be late.
But you should stay.

917
01:17:49,333 --> 01:17:50,753
Why does he keep doing this?

918
01:17:54,625 --> 01:17:55,705
I don't know.

919
01:18:00,041 --> 01:18:02,251
Have him call me
when you hear from him, OK?

920
01:18:04,041 --> 01:18:04,881
Yeah.

921
01:18:05,291 --> 01:18:06,581
-[Kate] Bye.
-Bye.

922
01:18:06,708 --> 01:18:08,708
[footsteps receding]

923
01:18:12,208 --> 01:18:14,288
[Amanda]
<i>I heard you beat the shit outta Roamer.</i>

924
01:18:16,583 --> 01:18:18,083
Why do you keep doing stuff like that?

925
01:18:18,166 --> 01:18:20,536
Aren't you tired of people
talking about you all the time?

926
01:18:22,166 --> 01:18:23,916
People are always gonna talk.

927
01:18:24,916 --> 01:18:26,166
It's their specialty.

928
01:18:29,583 --> 01:18:30,583
Are you OK?

929
01:18:34,125 --> 01:18:37,665
I don't know.
I feel like I keep messing things up,

930
01:18:37,750 --> 01:18:42,170
and I'm not sure
I know how to not do that.

931
01:18:42,625 --> 01:18:43,625
Does this work?

932
01:18:45,666 --> 01:18:47,456
It's better than the alternative.

933
01:18:54,500 --> 01:18:56,000
[knocking on door]

934
01:19:35,333 --> 01:19:37,253
[Kate] <i>Your girlfriend's pretty worried</i>
<i>about you.</i>

935
01:19:37,708 --> 01:19:39,628
She's been at the house all afternoon.

936
01:19:43,041 --> 01:19:44,041
What's going on?

937
01:19:49,083 --> 01:19:52,173
I don't... really remember...

938
01:19:53,125 --> 01:19:55,245
Dad that well.

939
01:19:56,833 --> 01:19:58,713
And everything I do...

940
01:20:01,041 --> 01:20:03,461
remember is... is bad.

941
01:20:07,208 --> 01:20:08,378
Are there any...

942
01:20:09,583 --> 01:20:11,753
good memories you have of him?

943
01:20:12,791 --> 01:20:13,831
[Kate sighs]

944
01:20:14,833 --> 01:20:17,923
Well, the fact that he would
beat the shit out of us

945
01:20:18,000 --> 01:20:19,830
kind of negated all the good times.

946
01:20:26,916 --> 01:20:29,496
But why was he like that?

947
01:20:29,583 --> 01:20:32,333
Was he like that because of us? Was he...

948
01:20:33,583 --> 01:20:34,883
like that because of Mom?

949
01:20:34,958 --> 01:20:37,378
He was like that
because he was a shitty person.

950
01:20:37,833 --> 01:20:39,833
[Finch] There has to be a reason, though.

951
01:20:39,916 --> 01:20:42,996
Because if there's a reason,
then he could get better.

952
01:20:43,083 --> 01:20:44,173
Something or...

953
01:20:45,500 --> 01:20:48,420
someone could make him better, right?

954
01:20:48,875 --> 01:20:51,875
I don't know. Who cares?
Dude, he's someone else's problem.

955
01:20:51,958 --> 01:20:53,998
Why are you asking me about Dad?

956
01:20:57,875 --> 01:20:59,285
What's going on, Finch?

957
01:21:03,541 --> 01:21:05,461
Come on. You can talk to me, man.

958
01:21:08,333 --> 01:21:10,133
Nothing, Kate.

959
01:21:10,208 --> 01:21:11,288
Sorry. Nothing.

960
01:21:12,666 --> 01:21:13,666
I'm good.

961
01:21:14,458 --> 01:21:16,918
Are you sure?
Because I have to open the bar,

962
01:21:17,000 --> 01:21:20,750
-but I can find someone to cover me.
-I'm good. [chuckles]

963
01:21:24,750 --> 01:21:26,500
You know I love you, right, Theo?

964
01:21:29,750 --> 01:21:30,670
I know.

965
01:21:47,208 --> 01:21:48,208
[door opens]

966
01:21:52,958 --> 01:21:54,418
[footsteps approaching]

967
01:22:13,791 --> 01:22:14,881
You scared me.

968
01:22:21,458 --> 01:22:22,918
What is all of this?

969
01:22:25,583 --> 01:22:27,253
[Finch] I'm trying to focus.

970
01:22:28,250 --> 01:22:29,580
[Violet] Focus on what?

971
01:22:30,916 --> 01:22:32,286
On staying awake.

972
01:22:34,916 --> 01:22:36,996
I don't understand what that means.

973
01:22:38,708 --> 01:22:40,168
Sometimes I...

974
01:22:41,125 --> 01:22:42,325
go blank.

975
01:22:44,166 --> 01:22:46,876
I... get into these dark moods.

976
01:22:48,041 --> 01:22:50,671
I think too fast
to keep track of anything,

977
01:22:51,750 --> 01:22:53,040
and then it's like...

978
01:22:54,208 --> 01:22:57,038
all my thoughts are gone at once.

979
01:22:58,458 --> 01:23:01,788
And sometimes,
if I put 'em up there, I can...

980
01:23:02,208 --> 01:23:04,328
focus and slow down, but...

981
01:23:07,291 --> 01:23:09,791
I can't right now. I can't.

982
01:23:11,958 --> 01:23:12,958
OK.

983
01:23:14,125 --> 01:23:15,915
[Finch] And this usually works.

984
01:23:16,000 --> 01:23:17,790
Maybe there's too much clutter.

985
01:23:21,333 --> 01:23:23,713
I can fix it. I just...

986
01:23:24,083 --> 01:23:27,003
I just need time to figure this out.

987
01:23:30,291 --> 01:23:33,291
-[Violet] I'm trying to help you.
-I don't need your help!

988
01:23:33,833 --> 01:23:36,543
This is on me! This isn't about you!

989
01:23:38,833 --> 01:23:40,713
You need to tell me what's wrong.

990
01:23:44,375 --> 01:23:45,455
You don't get it.

991
01:23:48,083 --> 01:23:49,583
[sobbing]

992
01:23:51,583 --> 01:23:52,673
You're right.

993
01:23:53,833 --> 01:23:55,083
I don't get it.

994
01:23:58,416 --> 01:24:00,036
Don't you know, Violet?

995
01:24:03,666 --> 01:24:04,876
I'm "The Freak."

996
01:24:08,916 --> 01:24:10,286
I'm fucked up!

997
01:24:22,875 --> 01:24:23,995
I need you to leave.

998
01:24:29,916 --> 01:24:30,876
Go!

999
01:24:33,875 --> 01:24:35,375
[footsteps receding]

1000
01:24:39,750 --> 01:24:40,960
[door opens]

1001
01:24:42,041 --> 01:24:43,041
[door closes]

1002
01:25:00,375 --> 01:25:01,745
[birds chirping]

1003
01:25:07,208 --> 01:25:09,208
[indistinct chattering]

1004
01:25:23,791 --> 01:25:25,251
[brakes squeak]

1005
01:25:35,125 --> 01:25:37,125
[ringing tone]

1006
01:25:39,458 --> 01:25:41,708
[voicemail]
<i>Hey, it's Finch. Leave a message.</i>

1007
01:25:41,791 --> 01:25:43,581
-[Violet sobbing]
-[voicemail beeps]

1008
01:25:43,666 --> 01:25:45,376
Hey, Finch. Um... [sobs]

1009
01:25:47,750 --> 01:25:49,250
I'm sorry.

1010
01:25:50,250 --> 01:25:51,830
I'm just sorry that I pushed.

1011
01:25:51,916 --> 01:25:53,666
And... I...

1012
01:25:54,916 --> 01:25:56,666
just need you to come back.

1013
01:26:00,958 --> 01:26:03,498
I just really need you to come back, OK?

1014
01:26:09,708 --> 01:26:11,708
[breathing heavily]

1015
01:26:30,750 --> 01:26:31,920
Hey, kiddo.

1016
01:26:32,750 --> 01:26:33,630
Hey.

1017
01:26:39,875 --> 01:26:40,825
Dad?

1018
01:26:43,333 --> 01:26:44,173
Yeah?

1019
01:26:48,041 --> 01:26:49,501
On Eleanor's birthday...

1020
01:26:53,958 --> 01:26:54,878
I...

1021
01:26:57,833 --> 01:26:59,253
I wasn't really thinking.

1022
01:27:04,791 --> 01:27:06,711
I found myself at the bridge.

1023
01:27:10,666 --> 01:27:12,416
